WEBVTT

00:04.394 --> 00:06.879
Previously on "Dead of Summer"...

00:07.634 --> 00:08.682
I got to go.

00:08.732 --> 00:09.796
What did I do? Cricket!

00:09.846 --> 00:10.797
Who are you?

00:10.847 --> 00:12.115
Look, you said you could accept me.

00:12.165 --> 00:13.949
- Blair...
- Every time I see you,

00:13.999 --> 00:14.974
you seem to be filming something.

00:15.024 --> 00:16.013
You know what they say.

00:16.062 --> 00:17.015
The camera never lies.

00:17.067 --> 00:18.442
I feel like I could talk
to you all night.

00:18.492 --> 00:20.318
Gross. She's like your mother's age.

00:20.473 --> 00:22.405
Deb might not be who she says she is.

00:22.455 --> 00:24.041
Deb is not Satanic.

00:24.153 --> 00:25.583
If she was, isn't Cricket right?

00:25.633 --> 00:26.703
Wouldn't she hide it?

00:26.753 --> 00:28.653
But I do know
something is going on here.

00:28.703 --> 00:30.521
You ever think it's possible...

00:30.571 --> 00:32.590
that some of it could be real?

00:32.640 --> 00:35.594
The Tall Man has said,
"It's only just begun."

00:43.673 --> 00:45.268
Do you expect me to talk?

00:45.318 --> 00:46.554
No, Mr. Bond.

00:46.604 --> 00:48.384
I expect you to die.

00:49.568 --> 00:51.274
Oh, check it out, Joel!

00:52.203 --> 00:55.174
Do you think I
could pass as 007 at prom?

00:55.753 --> 00:56.770
Maybe...

00:56.820 --> 00:58.405
If everyone there was blind.

00:58.455 --> 01:00.252
Oh, okay.

01:02.800 --> 01:03.978
You know, I'm gonna miss you, brother.

01:04.028 --> 01:06.072
A few more weeks,
you'll be off at camp, man.

01:06.122 --> 01:07.888
I wish you could come with me.

01:08.324 --> 01:10.275
Nah, I've had my own experience
with Stillwater.

01:10.325 --> 01:11.409
You got to experience it for yourself.

01:11.459 --> 01:15.260
As the geeky kid that nobody
can believe is related to you?

01:18.804 --> 01:20.763
Let's see them call you geeky in that.

01:22.689 --> 01:24.486
I could fit four of me in this.

01:24.536 --> 01:25.633
It depends how you wear it.

01:25.683 --> 01:28.392
Perception beats reality every time.

01:30.377 --> 01:32.778
I can't believe you're giving
me your favorite shirt.

01:32.828 --> 01:35.172
Just thank me when you win
your first Oscar, okay?

01:35.222 --> 01:37.386
Deal.
- My man.

